Python Data Types:


    1 Byte = 8bits

        1bit --> 0/1
        possible values can be stored in 1bit = two 

        8bit -->
        possible values can be stored in 8bit = 2.2.2.2.2.2.2.2 = 256

    Data Structuring 
        1. Managing storage efficiently

        Age = [0.1, 120] --> float --> 64bit -> 8Bytes

            Age --> 37 * 8

        Age = [0,1,..120] --> int --> 32bit -> 4Bytes

            Age --> 37 * 4

        1. Basic Data Types
            1. Character -- 1bit  
                1. plain characters 1Byte --> 8bits --> 256 
                2. Boolean characters 1bit --> True / False --> 0/1
            2. Integer 32bit
            3. float 64bit
            4. Double >64bit
            5. String --> collection of characters

        2. Advanced Data Types


Python is an implicit type casting

Variable: --> A name when its been assigned by any valid value
Type: --> type() is a python function which tells you about the data type of the variable
Explicit Type Casting --> Converting or casting data type of the variable explicitly


Strings:
    1. '' value assigning
    2. "" value assigning
    3. '''''' value assigning
    4. escape character --> \
        --> When you add \ in a string. the character which is just next to \ will be ignored


Literals --> value
    1. string Literals
    2. integer literals